h1. Features

<div class="summary">
<p>Gecode/R provides access to many, but not all, of "Gecode's 
features":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/modules.html.</p>
</div>

h2. Supported platforms

Ruby 1.8.6 on
* Windows (tested with the "one-click Ruby installer":http://rubyinstaller.rubyforge.org/wiki/wiki.pl)
* Linux
* OS X

h2. Supported Gecode features 

The following things are supported by Gecode/R.

* Boolean variables with the following constraints
** "Simple relation":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntRelBool.html
** "Linear":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntLinearBool.html
* Finite domain integer variables with the following constraints
** "Arithmetic":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntArith.html except for square and square root
** "Cardinality":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntCard.html except for the ones involving more than one variable array
** "Channel":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntChannel.html except for channeling between integer variables and boolean variables
** "Distinct":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntDistinct.html
** "Domain":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntDomain.html
** "Element":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntElement.html
** "Linear":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntLinearInt.html
** "Simple relation":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntRelInt.html
** "Sorted":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntSorted.html
** "Extensional":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntExt.html except for DFA versions
* Finite integer sets with the following constraints
** "Distinct":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelSetDistinct.html
** "Domain":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelSetDom.html
** "Connection constraints to finite domain variables":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelSetConnect.html except for channeling with boolean variables
** "Relation":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelSetRel.html
** "Set selection":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelSetSelection.html
** "Set operation":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelSetRelOp.html
* Branching selection
* Branch and bound, and depth first search
* Reification, propagation strength and propagation kind


h2. Features not supported

The following are some notable features that are included in Gecode but _not_
in Gecode/R (but might be in the future).

* Finite integer sets with complete domain representation and all their constraints
* Unsupported integer constraints
** The exceptions noted in the list of supported constraints
** "Scheduling":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntScheduling.html
** "Graph":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelIntGraph.html
* Unsupported set constraints
** The exceptions noted in the list of supported constraints
** "Convexity":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelSetConvex.html
** "Sequence":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelSetSequence.html
** "Projector":http://www.gecode.org/gecode-doc-search-2.1.1/group__TaskModelSetProjector.html
* Limited discrepancy search
* Custom propagators and branching strategies
* Search statistics
* Reflection

